Description: Terra Sigillata wheel-made pottery sherd with a fine glossy red slip. Fine yellow pottery fabric.
Curator's comments: Imperial Roman red slip fine tableware sherd of Eastern Terra Sigillata A ware from Syria, dated c. 1-150AD (Hayes 1985, form Atlal 40/53/54 or similar). Hayes, J. W. 1985. Sigillate Orientali. In Encicliopedia dell 'arte antica, atlate della forme ceramica. II ceramica fine Romana nel bacio Mediterraneo (Tarlo ellenism eprimo imperio), pp. 1-96. Rome.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IF.075) (Phase 3)
